data_cleaned <- data[-c(68, 87, 101), ]
mod_cleaned <- lm(Accounts.reached ~ Who + More_Specific + 
    Ugly + Tags + pgn_nationals_tag + fyic_tag + farmer_tag + 
    brands_tag + Profile_Visits + Follows, data = data_cleaned)
#summary(mod_cleaned)
predictions <- predict(mod_cleaned, newdata = data_cleaned)

The factors that have the greatest correlation to the account reach in a positive way: who posted it, tagging two brands, more profile visits, and follows.

The factors that have the greatestcorrelation to the account reach in a negative way: holiday posts and ugly posts.

Residual standard error: On average, the models predictions are off by about 322 accounts reached.

Adjusted R-squared: After adjusting for the number of predictors, the model explains about 75.28% of the variance. This is very good and suggests the model is well-fitting.
